[00:00.000]--- lesson 12  Life on a desert island 荒岛生活
[00:04.571]Most of us have formed an unrealistic picture of life on a desert island.^我们许多人对于荒岛生活有一种不切实际的想法。
[00:10.371]We sometimes imagine a desert island to be a sort of paradise where the sun always shines.^我们有时想象荒岛是阳光终日普照的天堂。
[00:18.260]Life there is simple and good.^在那里，生活简单又美好。
[00:20.793]Ripe fruit falls from the trees and you never have to work.^成熟的水果从树上掉下来，人们根本无需劳动。
[00:25.783]The other side of the picture is quite the opposite.^另一种想法恰恰相反，
[00:29.544]Life on a desert island is wretched.^认为荒岛生活很可怕，
[00:32.392]You either starve to death or live like Robinson Crusoe, Waiting for a boat which never comes.^要么饿死，要么像鲁滨孙那样，天天盼船来，却总不见船影。
[00:40.307]Perhaps there is an element of truth in both these pictures,^也许，这两种想象都有可信之处。
[00:44.591]but few of us have had the opportunity to find out.^但很少有人能有机会去弄个究竟。
[00:48.379]Two men who recently spent five days on a coral island wished they had stayed there longer.^最近有两个人在一座珊瑚岛上呆了5天，他们真希望在那儿再多呆一些日子。
[00:56.216]They were taking a badly damaged boat from the Virgin Islands to Miami to have it repaired.^他们驾着一条严重损坏的小船从维尔京群岛去迈阿密修理。
[01:02.903]During the journey, their boat began to sink.^途中，船开始下沉，
[01:06.456]They quickly loaded a small rubber dinghy with food, matches, and cans of beer^他们迅速把食物、火柴、罐装啤酒往一只救生筏上装。
[01:12.934]and rowed for a few miles across the Caribbean until they arrived at a tiny coral island.^然后在加勒比海上划行了几英里，到了一座珊瑚岛上。
[01:19.856]There were hardly any trees on the island and there was no water, but this did not prove to be a problem.^岛上几乎没有一颗树，也没有淡水，但这不算什么问题。
[01:27.667]The men collected rainwater in the rubber dinghy.^他们用像皮艇蓄积雨水。
[01:31.376]As they had brought a spear gun with them, they had plenty to eat.^由于他们随身带了一支捕鱼枪，因此，吃饭不愁。
[01:35.869]They caught lobster and fish every day，and, as one of them put it 'ate like kings'.^他们天天捕捉龙虾和鱼，正如其中一位所说，吃得“像国王一样好”。
[01:43.340]When a passing tanker rescued them five days later, both men were genuinely sorry that they had to leave.^5天后，一条油轮从那儿路过，搭救了他们。这二位不得不离开那个荒岛时，还真的感到遗憾呢！
